1. Definitions

"Affiliate" means an entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common
control with another entity. "Control" means ownership of more than fifty
percent (50%) of voting interests or the power to direct management.

"Annual Revenue" means the gross revenue of an Organization and its Affiliates
for the most recent completed fiscal year or, if a completed fiscal year is not
available, the trailing twelve (12) months.

"Commercial License" means a separate written agreement with the Licensor that
grants rights beyond this License.

"Competing Offering" means a product or service offered to third parties where
the Licensed Work, or a substantially similar backend, database, or developer
platform service, is a primary or material part of the value offered.

"Educational Institution" means a school, college, university, public research
institution, or similar accredited educational or academic body.

"Enterprise Threshold" means that, during a calendar month, both of the
following are true for an Organization and its Affiliates:

1. Annual Revenue exceeds USD $10,000,000.
2. Monthly Active Users exceed 500.

"Free Use" means use authorized by Section 3 of this License without payment.

"Hosted Service" means a hosted, managed, software-as-a-service, platform, API,
or cloud offering made available to third parties.

"Licensor" means each copyright holder licensing the Licensed Work under this
License.

"Monthly Active User" or "MAU" means a unique natural person, internal or
external, who in a calendar month accesses, authenticates with, or causes
material application activity backed by the Licensed Work, whether directly or
through an application, service, device, or integration operated by or for the
benefit of an Organization. Purely automated internal service accounts, bots,
and background jobs that are not acting on behalf of a unique natural person do
not count as separate Monthly Active Users.

"Nonprofit Organization" means an entity organized and operated primarily for
charitable, educational, religious, scientific, or similar public-benefit
purposes and not primarily for private commercial gain.

"Organization" means a legal entity and its Affiliates.

"Permitted Use" means Free Use or Trial Use that complies with this License.

"Trial Use" means the limited use permitted during the Trial Period described in
Section 4.

"Trial Period" means the one-time ninety (90) day period that starts when an
Organization first exceeds the Enterprise Threshold.

