7. Measurement, Good-Faith Counting, and Records

If your rights under this License depend on Annual Revenue or Monthly Active
Users, you must determine eligibility in good faith using commercially
reasonable methods.

When exact Monthly Active User counts are unavailable, you may estimate them
using authenticated identities, user or tenant identifiers, request activity,
device or browser identifiers, or similar operational telemetry that reasonably
approximates unique natural-person usage.

You must keep records reasonably sufficient to support your good-faith Annual
Revenue and Monthly Active User determinations for at least twelve (12) months
after each relevant period.

